'''Heinrich Lausberg''' (12 October 1912 in [[Aachen]]; died 11 April 1992 in [[Münster]]) was a German [[rhetoric]]ian, [[Classical philology|classical philologist]] and [[Historical linguistics|historical linguist]] specialising in [[Romance studies]]. His 1960 treatise ''[https://books.google.com/books?id=rzESGVfBEWIC Handbook of literary rhetoric]'',<ref>Leiden, Brill, 1988.</ref> is considered one of the most complete and detailed summaries of classical rhetoric from the perspective of [[Quintillian]]'s [[quadripartita ratio|four operations]].<ref>[[Groupe µ]] (1970) ''[[A General Rhetoric]]'', Introduction</ref> His daughter, Marion Lausberg, is a classical philologist, too.

