'''Jeannine Auboyer''' (1912 - 1990) was a French curator of the [[Musée Guimet]] (1965–80) in [[Paris]], who made several [[Archaeology|archaeological]] expeditions to [[India]] and [[Cambodia]] and wrote numerous French titles on history.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.britannica.com/contributor/Jeannine-Auboyer/119|title=Jeannine Auboyer|website=Encyclopedia Britannica|access-date=2017-01-17}}</ref> She is known for ''Daily Life in Ancient India'' (French: ''La Vie quotidienne dans l'Inde ancienne)'', a record of the ancient Indian rituals and customs, many of which are preserved in Indian society today.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Jarrige|first=Jean-François|title=Jeannine Auboyer 1912-1990|url=http://www.persee.fr/doc/arasi_0004-3958_1991_num_46_1_1308|journal=Arts asiatiques|volume=46|issue=1}}</ref>

