[[File:JeroglificodeTepeticpac.jpg|thumb|Glyph of Tepeticpac]]
'''Tepeticpac''' was one of the four ''[[altepetl]]'' (polities) that made up the [[confederation]] of [[Tlaxcala (altepetl)|Tlaxcala]].  It was the northwest-most [[altepetl]], located west of the Atzompa river and north of [[Quiahuiztlan]]. 

The site is in the present day state of [[Tlaxcala]] in central [[Mexico]].

